A deputy principal at Edalinceba Primary School in Ekurhuleni has been shot dead inside his office on Tuesday. It is alleged that several shots were fired in the administration block and that the victim was a senior member of staff at the school. Netcare spokesperson Nick Dollman said, “paramedics attended to a 55-year-old man who had been shot more than once. Sadly, the man sustained severe injuries and died prior the arrival of the paramedics.” The incident was attended by the SAPS and Ekurhuleni EMS and are yet to provide more information. -TNA Reporter 